Description: piRNAs (PIWI-interacting RNAs) and their PIWI protein partners play a key role in fertility and 
    maintaining genome integrity by restricting mobile genetic elements (transposons) in germ cells. 
    PiRNAs originate from genomic regions which are called piRNA clusters. The piRNA Cluster Builder (PICB) 
    identifies genomic regions with a high density of piRNAs. This construction of piRNA clusters is performed 
    through stepwise integration of unique and multimapping piRNAs.
